[["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/section[1]/div[1]/div[1]/article[1]/div[1]/p[1]/text()[1]","Berrien County Sheriff Paul Bailey is seeking re-election. He’s going for his fifth term as sheriff in the August Republican primary. Bailey says it’s been an honor serving as sheriff for the past 15 years, adding he’s seeking re-election because he wants to continue programs in place, while looking for new ideas and ways of serving the community."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/section[1]/div[1]/div[1]/article[1]/div[1]/p[2]/text()[1]","Among his accomplishments as sheriff in 2015, Bailey lists an emergency management simulation of an attack on the Palisades nuclear power plant, organizing school safety drills,  securing grants from Homeland Security, implementing a new electronic records system, and training sheriffs deputies to save the lives of overdose victims with Narcan. Bailey took office as sheriff in 2001."]]